node.title: Phoenix rocked by COVID outbreak: Next two A-League fixtures postponed
node.description: And the FFA Cup semi-final against the Victory is also at risk.
node.content: ["The Wellington Phoenix\u2019s next two A-League men\u2019s matches have been postponed because of several positive COVID-19 cases inside the camp.", "Eight players have tested positive, while two other players and a staff member are close contacts and have to be isolated for seven days.", "This is in addition to the two players and staff member who tested positive last week.", "It means the Phoenix will be unable to field a squad for tomorrow\u2019s round nine match against the Newcastle Jets in Sydney or next weekend\u2019s clash against Perth Glory so the A-Leagues have agreed to postpone both fixtures.", "The A-Leagues will work with all the clubs involved to reschedule the matches for later in the season.", "The Phoenix have also asked Football Australia if the men\u2019s FFA Cup semi-final against Melbourne Victory, scheduled to be played next week, can be pushed back."]
